com.tianscar.javasound.midi.spi

Interface MidiResourceReader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JDKMidiResourceReader

    public interface MidiResourceReader
    A MidiResourceReader supplies MIDI resource-reading services. Classes implementing this interface can parse the format information from one or more types of MIDI resource, and can produce a Sequence object from resources of these types.

      • getMidiFileFormat

        javax.sound.midi.MidiFileFormat getMidiFileFormat(java.lang.ClassLoader resourceLoader,
                                                  java.lang.String name)
                                           throws javax.sound.midi.InvalidMidiDataException,
                                                  java.io.IOException
        Obtains the MIDI file format of the resource provided. The resource must point to valid MIDI file data.
        Parameters:
        resourceLoader - the ClassLoader to load resource
        name - the resource name from which file format information should be extracted
        Returns:
        a MidiFileFormat object describing the MIDI file format
        Throws:
        javax.sound.midi.InvalidMidiDataException - if the resource does not point to valid MIDI file data recognized by the system
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O exception occurs

      • getSequence

        javax.sound.midi.Sequence getSequence(java.lang.ClassLoader resourceLoader,
                                      java.lang.String name)
                               throws javax.sound.midi.InvalidMidiDataException,
                                      java.io.IOException
        Obtains a MIDI sequence from the resource provided. The resource must point to valid MIDI file data.
        Parameters:
        resourceLoader - the ClassLoader to load resource
        name - the resource name for which the Sequence should be constructed
        Returns:
        a Sequence object based on the MIDI file data pointed to by the resource
        Throws:
        javax.sound.midi.InvalidMidiDataException - if the resource does not point to valid MIDI file data recognized by the system
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O exception occurs
